11
00:01:01,817 --> 00:01:02,718
[SPEAKER_17]: Perfect, thank you.

12
00:01:02,778 --> 00:01:06,362
[SPEAKER_17]: Could you just present the petition for us and give us an idea of what you're looking for?

13
00:01:07,083 --> 00:01:09,586
[SPEAKER_10]: Well, so it's my father-in-law.

14
00:01:09,726 --> 00:01:19,897
[SPEAKER_10]: He's 92 years old, and he lives on Lookout Road, and he lives at 20 Lookout Road, and he doesn't have a driveway.

15
00:01:21,217 --> 00:01:37,568
[SPEAKER_10]: And a couple of times he's come home, he normally is able to park in front of his house, but there have been times when he's come home, he still drives, he still does his own shopping, but one time, or a few times, people have been parked in front of his house.

16
00:01:38,468 --> 00:01:41,911
[SPEAKER_10]: And now he's got to lug the groceries down the street.

17
00:01:42,691 --> 00:01:52,458
[SPEAKER_10]: And so I said, you know, I've seen, you know, they have handicapped parking signs where they'll they'll reserve the spot for you.

18
00:01:52,538 --> 00:01:57,982
[SPEAKER_10]: So I said, if you want, I'll submit the paperwork and see if if they if they agree with it.

19
00:01:58,743 --> 00:02:00,484
[SPEAKER_10]: Like I said, he doesn't have a driveway.

20
00:02:00,544 --> 00:02:02,005
[SPEAKER_10]: He's forced to park in the street.

21
00:02:03,586 --> 00:02:12,869
[SPEAKER_10]: Other people, they have driveways, but a lot of times there's the number of people that can park in the driveway is limited, maybe only one or two cars.

22
00:02:13,369 --> 00:02:17,170
[SPEAKER_10]: And they have kids now and the kids are driving as well, so.

23
00:02:17,190 --> 00:02:20,451
[SPEAKER_17]: Okay, I appreciate that presentation.

24
00:02:20,591 --> 00:02:27,613
