[SPEAKER_05]: I'm going to ask you to unmute yourself and... I see you right in the middle of Romero.

365
00:27:58,116 --> 00:27:58,836
[SPEAKER_17]: Yep, we're getting there.

366
00:28:00,112 --> 00:28:00,672
[SPEAKER_17]: Sorry about that.

367
00:28:00,712 --> 00:28:01,252
[SPEAKER_12]: Can you hear me now?

368
00:28:01,753 --> 00:28:02,593
[SPEAKER_17]: Yes, we can hear you.

369
00:28:02,653 --> 00:28:03,173
[SPEAKER_17]: Welcome.

370
00:28:03,393 --> 00:28:08,035
[SPEAKER_17]: And if you would, could you please present your petition to the commission?

371
00:28:08,636 --> 00:28:08,896
[SPEAKER_12]: Sure.

372
00:28:08,916 --> 00:28:11,937
[SPEAKER_12]: This is for my son.

373
00:28:11,957 --> 00:28:16,039
[SPEAKER_12]: He's unfortunately still at work today.

374
00:28:16,859 --> 00:28:22,782
[SPEAKER_12]: And he's a recent graduate, 2021, from the Medford Vocational and Technical High School.

375
00:28:23,502 --> 00:28:24,862
[SPEAKER_12]: And he graduated from the

376
00:28:26,795 --> 00:28:34,200
[SPEAKER_12]: carpentry program, and he immediately got a job after graduation with a carpentry company that's based in Newton.

377
00:28:34,900 --> 00:28:45,887
[SPEAKER_12]: And after about six, eight months, he did well enough that they wanted him to go to all of their different job sites throughout sort of greater Boston area.

378
00:28:46,367 --> 00:28:54,693
[SPEAKER_12]: And so they gave him a company van to carry around all of his tools, his saws, his saw horses, ladders, et cetera.

379
00:28:55,413 --> 00:29:01,077
[SPEAKER_12]: And so he needs to park it at our house where he is still living.

380
00:29:02,037 --> 00:29:08,381
[SPEAKER_12]: And what he needs is a place to park on the street overnight so that he can get up.

381
00:29:08,881 --> 00:29:13,584
[SPEAKER_12]: He usually gets up around 5.30, 6 o'clock in the morning and drives to his job.

382
00:29:14,325 --> 00:29:15,045
[SPEAKER_12]: We do have a...

383
00:29:17,108 --> 00:29:24,030
[SPEAKER_12]: off-street parking with the driveway, but both my wife and I have our cars, and we park in those spaces.

384
00:29:24,930 --> 00:29:33,852
[SPEAKER_12]: My wife was supposed to be here today, his mother, but she actually is at the hospital where she has been called.

385
00:29:34,252 --> 00:29:38,553
[SPEAKER_12]: And this is one of the concerns that we have, is that we would need to

386
00:29:39,613 --> 00:29:43,974
[SPEAKER_12]: you know, be able to leave quite quickly so that she can get to a hospital in any emergency.

387
00:29:44,754 --> 00:29:56,498
[SPEAKER_12]: So what we're asking for is just a variance to allow him to park his commercial van outside of our home, right where you're pointing, and be able to leave it there overnight.

388
00:29:58,698 --> 00:30:00,319
[SPEAKER_17]: Thank you for presenting.

389
00:30:00,339 --> 00:30:05,460
[SPEAKER_17]: Commissioner, any questions of the petitioner?

390
00:30:16,255 --> 00:30:23,198
[SPEAKER_15]: I don't have it in the petitioner, but I thought we had come to a decision on these commercial spaces in residential neighborhoods already.

391
00:30:23,939 --> 00:30:26,180
[SPEAKER_15]: Are they still open for us to discuss and approve?

392
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:30,302
[SPEAKER_01]: I think this is the problem.

393
00:30:30,782 --> 00:30:37,245
[SPEAKER_01]: We could ask the petitioner why can't his wife park on the street and his son park in the driveway.

394
00:30:39,225 --> 00:30:41,306
[SPEAKER_01]: That would solve the problem, obviously.

395
00:30:43,516 --> 00:30:56,220
[SPEAKER_01]: I think that this is commercial vehicles is one of our issue problems that we need, that I don't think we all agree on how we deal with.

396
00:30:57,520 --> 00:31:03,362
[SPEAKER_01]: And it's not clear that it's at a level that we're able to serve, fix it on one-off variants.

397
00:31:03,402 --> 00:31:05,322
[SPEAKER_01]: We've had them come in front of us before.

398
00:31:05,342 --> 00:31:11,124
[SPEAKER_15]: I seem to remember the last time we had this, we referred them to city council.

