473
00:37:40,336 --> 00:37:48,321
[SPEAKER_01]: In zoning we said that there were accessory wait I had it on my screen a second ago I'll get it but there was um

474
00:37:50,139 --> 00:37:57,925
[SPEAKER_01]: In zoning, we used under accessory uses, home occupations had allowed and not allowed.

475
00:37:57,945 --> 00:38:02,608
[SPEAKER_01]: And it said, here's it does not.

476
00:38:05,230 --> 00:38:13,936
[SPEAKER_01]: Prohibited accessory uses, overnight parking except an enclosed garage of any commercial vehicle with a gross vehicle weight of more than 15,000 pounds.

477
00:38:16,355 --> 00:38:26,304
[SPEAKER_01]: That's I think based on my energy work, 15,000 pounds is a line that is often used to delineate a large vehicle from a smaller vehicle.

478
00:38:28,626 --> 00:38:42,419
[SPEAKER_01]: What we actually put in the zoning implied that if you were a home occupation and you had an accessory use, actually this is accessory use in all districts,

479
00:38:44,793 --> 00:38:49,094
[SPEAKER_01]: And it just listed prohibited accessory use, overnight parking of any commercial vehicle.

480
00:38:49,374 --> 00:38:59,056
[SPEAKER_01]: So this would actually imply, because it's in zoning, even outside, like if you had a private driveway, you couldn't park something over 15,000 pounds.

481
00:38:59,116 --> 00:39:03,656
[SPEAKER_04]: That sounds like a decent delineation.

482
00:39:03,996 --> 00:39:12,318
[SPEAKER_04]: I guess if you went that road for the on street, you'd likely have to, to be fair, not a case by case, you'd say commercial.

483
00:39:13,117 --> 00:39:26,440
[SPEAKER_04]: Overnight under 15,000 over 15,000 split that delineation somehow so that then you had at least something to follow Well, right now there's an absence of that right right now It's just all commercial vehicles overnight.

484
00:39:26,720 --> 00:39:31,681
[SPEAKER_04]: They have a plate and the plate could be on the passenger car or 18 wheeler Right.

485
00:39:32,102 --> 00:39:33,082
[SPEAKER_17]: So that is that is

486
00:39:34,298 --> 00:39:54,223
[SPEAKER_17]: some degree correct I'm just reading so it is in the traffic commission rules and regulations and I have that in front of me they define a commercial vehicle as a gross vehicle weight in excess of 6,000 pounds so that's the first out of it so the standing the ordinance is this the standing or parking of any commercial and or overweight and or oversized

487
00:39:54,983 --> 00:40:01,864
[SPEAKER_17]: motor vehicle whether occupied or not is prohibited overnight on any street within the city of Medford between the hours of 12 midnight and 6 a.m.

488
00:40:02,404 --> 00:40:14,546
[SPEAKER_17]: Additionally no commercial vehicle shall be allowed to park on any city street regardless of time of day in excess of one hour unless the operator said vehicle is conducting a delivery of goods or services directly related to their business.

489
00:40:15,627 --> 00:40:21,988
[SPEAKER_17]: The above restrictions shall also apply to the standing or parking of overweight in excess of 85

490
00:40:23,328 --> 00:40:35,934
[SPEAKER_17]: hundred pounds gross vehicle weight and or oversized motor vehicles exceeding 20 feet in length and or eight feet width and or eight feet in height regardless of registration classification.

491
00:40:36,554 --> 00:40:41,237
[SPEAKER_17]: Goes on to just list no trailers regardless of size may be parked in any city streets.

492
00:40:42,497 --> 00:40:47,620
[SPEAKER_17]: It also defines what a commercial motor vehicle would be with regards to signage on the vehicle.

493
00:40:48,080 --> 00:40:52,262
[SPEAKER_17]: So anything exceeding six inches by 15 inches length would be considered a

494
00:40:52,982 --> 00:40:54,183
[SPEAKER_17]: commercial motor vehicle.

495
00:40:55,263 --> 00:40:58,445
[SPEAKER_17]: I think I got the gist of it here.

496
00:40:58,485 --> 00:41:04,769
[SPEAKER_17]: That's what we're working on and that is what we have had in place for quite some time.

497
00:41:04,809 --> 00:41:06,009
[SPEAKER_17]: This was done over in 2002.

498
00:41:09,071 --> 00:41:10,492
[SPEAKER_01]: What do we think those were up to?

499
00:41:10,512 --> 00:41:16,795
[SPEAKER_01]: Because I was thinking that when I heard those numbers that they're dated given the size of vehicles these days.

500
00:41:17,235 --> 00:41:21,878
[SPEAKER_01]: Although from a sustainability perspective, I'm happy to discriminate against large vehicles.

501
00:41:26,707 --> 00:41:27,889
[SPEAKER_17]: Hey, stand by just for you.

502
00:41:27,909 --> 00:41:28,450
[SPEAKER_17]: 1 more thing here.

503
00:41:28,470 --> 00:41:29,872
[SPEAKER_17]: That's going to probably help us.

504
00:42:04,567 --> 00:42:04,807
[SPEAKER_17]: Okay.

505
00:42:04,827 --> 00:42:15,979
[SPEAKER_17]: I'm surprised I'm not aware of this, but a Medford resident may apply for a commercial vehicle parking permit if the following conditions are met.

506
00:42:16,739 --> 00:42:19,102
[SPEAKER_17]: The applicant must be a resident of the City of Medford.

507
00:42:20,147 --> 00:42:24,091
[SPEAKER_17]: The motor vehicle is properly registered and insured in Massachusetts.

508
00:42:24,632 --> 00:42:27,815
[SPEAKER_17]: Proof of such must be submitted at the time of the application process.

509
00:42:28,516 --> 00:42:38,185
[SPEAKER_17]: The motor vehicle must comply within the dimensional standards as defined in the Medford Traffic Commission Rules and Regulations Article 5, Section 12, which is what I just read.

510
00:42:39,063 --> 00:42:42,789
[SPEAKER_17]: The motor vehicle must be owned by a partnership, trust or corporation.

511
00:42:43,389 --> 00:42:50,260
[SPEAKER_17]: Motor vehicles owned or registered under a doing business as are prohibited from permitting under the section.

512
00:42:50,861 --> 00:42:52,363
[SPEAKER_17]: The motor vehicle shall not have

513
00:42:53,610 --> 00:42:56,933
[SPEAKER_17]: excuse me, the motor vehicle shall not have five or more wheels.

514
00:42:57,913 --> 00:43:13,145
[SPEAKER_17]: The applicant must submit a notarized letter on company entity letterhead stating the vehicle in question has been used, has been issued to the applicant for their sole use and the application must include the name, title and phone number of the applicant's immediate supervisor.

515
00:43:14,110 --> 00:43:21,914
[SPEAKER_17]: The motor vehicle may not have lettering, markings or signs affixed or attached used for the identification or advertisement of a business, goods or services.

516
00:43:22,375 --> 00:43:31,340
[SPEAKER_17]: The motor vehicle may not have ladders, tools or equipment attached, affixed or carried on the exterior of the motor vehicle or in the case of a pickup truck in the bed area.

517
00:43:32,080 --> 00:43:41,164
[SPEAKER_17]: The vehicle shall be submitted for inspections, which is automatic, and only one permit shall be issued per address, and the permit shall be valid on the street where the applicant resides.

518
00:43:41,785 --> 00:43:44,006
[SPEAKER_17]: Trailers may not be attached to the motor vehicle.

519
00:43:44,846 --> 00:43:51,129
[SPEAKER_17]: The fee for such permit shall be $100 and will expire on December 31st of each issuing year.

520
00:43:54,411 --> 00:43:56,612
[SPEAKER_01]: So that's in our rules and regulations?

521
00:43:56,672 --> 00:43:57,692
[SPEAKER_01]: It's in the paperwork.

522
00:43:58,733 --> 00:43:58,993
[SPEAKER_17]: Yes.

