01:00:59,379 --> 01:01:01,640
[SPEAKER_17]: to approve a commercial vehicle variance.

721
01:01:05,542 --> 01:01:08,084
[SPEAKER_03]: Oh, commercial vehicle.

722
01:01:08,144 --> 01:01:12,806
[SPEAKER_15]: Can we put into the motion what we're varying, clarifying what?

723
01:01:13,286 --> 01:01:15,347
[SPEAKER_15]: I think we're just using the permit, aren't we?

724
01:01:15,427 --> 01:01:15,647
[SPEAKER_17]: Yes.

725
01:01:16,428 --> 01:01:19,889
[SPEAKER_17]: Well, we're approving the permit, but it has to be a variance because it has lettering on the vehicle.

726
01:01:21,650 --> 01:01:22,951
[SPEAKER_06]: Oh, okay.

727
01:01:23,391 --> 01:01:24,232
[SPEAKER_17]: All right.

728
01:01:24,252 --> 01:01:26,693
[SPEAKER_17]: So, motion would be to approve

729
01:01:29,425 --> 01:01:36,150
[SPEAKER_17]: a commercial vehicle parking permit variance of Vicus Romero 93 Walcott Street.

730
01:01:37,351 --> 01:01:39,133
[SPEAKER_17]: Is that your motion, Commissioner Hunt?

731
01:01:40,173 --> 01:01:40,454
[SPEAKER_01]: Yes.

732
01:01:41,454 --> 01:01:42,415
[SPEAKER_17]: Do I have a second?

733
01:01:48,680 --> 01:01:49,100
[SPEAKER_06]: All right.

734
01:01:49,281 --> 01:01:50,061
[SPEAKER_06]: I'll do it, Steve.

735
01:01:50,762 --> 01:01:51,102
[SPEAKER_06]: Second.

736
01:01:51,242 --> 01:01:51,682
[SPEAKER_15]: Yeah.

737
01:01:51,803 --> 01:01:52,543
[SPEAKER_15]: I'll be candid.

738
01:01:52,623 --> 01:01:58,788
[SPEAKER_15]: I'm reluctantly approving this just because I think this is something we need to think about as a team, and I hate that a homeowner would support it.

739
01:01:59,453 --> 01:02:08,001
[SPEAKER_15]: but I really challenge us in 2024 to start prioritizing these things and fixing them, because I don't necessarily like these subjective determinations.

740
01:02:08,161 --> 01:02:09,843
[SPEAKER_15]: I don't even know what the lettering looks like.

741
01:02:09,963 --> 01:02:15,368
[SPEAKER_15]: I presume that it looks fine, but what's gonna be un-fine one day?

742
01:02:16,469 --> 01:02:19,672
[SPEAKER_15]: I don't wanna necessarily second the motion, but I will support it today.

743
01:02:19,692 --> 01:02:23,095
[SPEAKER_06]: That's okay, I seconded it, we're good.

744
01:02:26,188 --> 01:02:34,171
[SPEAKER_06]: I think it's good that we should take a look and I think that we're talking about it in our regular meetings on the administration level.

745
01:02:35,372 --> 01:02:41,454
[SPEAKER_17]: And as the chair, I'm going to go on the record that I have some real concerns about this and where it goes, but it is on the record here.

746
01:02:41,494 --> 01:02:48,057
[SPEAKER_17]: I mean, it does fall under the permit parking, so the overnight vehicle, commercial vehicle parking permit.

747
01:02:48,077 --> 01:02:50,358
[SPEAKER_17]: So I'll have a roll call vote.

748
01:02:50,418 --> 01:02:51,258
[SPEAKER_02]: Commissioner McGiven?

749
01:02:51,278 --> 01:02:51,338
[SPEAKER_02]: Yes.

750
01:02:52,977 --> 01:02:53,757
[SPEAKER_02]: Commissioner Hunt?

751
01:02:54,498 --> 01:02:54,798
[SPEAKER_02]: Yes.

752
01:02:55,318 --> 01:02:56,419
[SPEAKER_02]: Commissioner Brzezinski?

753
01:02:56,899 --> 01:02:57,179
[SPEAKER_17]: Yes.

754
01:02:58,139 --> 01:02:58,780
[SPEAKER_02]: Chief Buckley?

755
01:02:59,220 --> 01:02:59,500
[SPEAKER_17]: Yes.

756
01:03:00,200 --> 01:03:01,321
[SPEAKER_17]: A vote of four to nothing.

757
01:03:01,341 --> 01:03:02,801
[SPEAKER_17]: The motion is approved.

758
01:03:03,122 --> 01:03:08,644
