[SPEAKER_04]: I understand what you're saying in there.

866
01:11:35,395 --> 01:11:42,860
[SPEAKER_04]: So yeah, this is on streets that are used to more space, they'll say if a car parks opposite them, they can't get out.

867
01:11:43,460 --> 01:11:50,764
[SPEAKER_04]: But in this very street, the middle block apart between Brogan and Tainter, there are driveways that aren't opposite one another.

868
01:11:50,804 --> 01:11:54,787
[SPEAKER_04]: So a driveway opposite, a car park opposite, and they somehow make it work.

869
01:11:55,507 --> 01:11:58,609
[SPEAKER_04]: So I'm just using the local example of the block right here.

870
01:12:00,576 --> 01:12:06,304
[SPEAKER_04]: all the driveways on either side of park in this middle block are not aligned with one another directly opposite each other.

871
01:12:07,245 --> 01:12:13,614
